The regex expression to extract a three character code from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm" would be:
`[A-Za-z0-9]{3}\.[uU][sS]?[fF][mM]`
This regular expression will match any three characters (either upper or lower case letters or digits) followed by a hyphen, then the filename extension ".usfm". The square brackets `[]` represent character classes, and the curly braces `{}` specify the number of occurrences. Here, `[A-Za-z0-9]` matches any letter or digit, `{3}` specifies exactly three characters, `[uU][sS]?[fF][mM]` ensures that the extension is ".usfm". The capitalized letters are used to make sure it's case insensitive.
